The Dance House is a party format where students can experience the compelling atmosphere of a community celebration and experience dancing to live music performed by agile instrumentalists. Each meeting the Dance House format focuses on one dance or board game through a special workshop.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to learn traditional dances in its natural environment with live music by using the method of active participation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student after having attended the course can do the following: - have obtained the basic steps of Estonian dances; - can differntiate between different dances by melody.
